Scope Statement: This is a more elaborate narrative of the work and includes the below: 
Project Objectives
Project Description
Requirements defined in previous section
Major deliverables to be produced
Criteria that deliverables must meet  if they are to be accepted
Known constraints
Assumptions

It is a useful tool to outline the project deliverables and identify the constraints, assumptions, and key success factors. 

Feasibility Study: This is the analysis used in measuring the ability and likelihood to complete a project succefully inclduing all relevent
factors. It must account for facors that affect it such as economic, technological, legal and scheduling factors. 
